Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.37,0:00:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom Use your head Keep thinking it you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.58,0:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.54,0:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On June 5, 1942, Japan was defeated in the Battle of Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.57,0:02:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They lost four aircraft carriers: Kaga, Akagi, Soryu, and Hiryu, as well as one heavy cruiser, 322 aircraft, and 3,500 soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.54,0:02:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the US military lost 150 aircraft and 300 soldiers, but one aircraft carrier: Yorktown was wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorktown was attacked twice by the Japanese, but only the engine was damaged and the hull was slightly scratched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The submarine I-168, commanded by Captain Tanabe, must put an end to this Yorktown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.23,0:03:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Five hours after receiving the order, 1-168 continued its run 150 nautical miles northeast of Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But can they really meet their enemies in the vast ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.71,0:03:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Radar was not heavily in use at that time. They can only rely on nautical charts, binoculars, and beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Submarine I-168 (Episode 12)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.13,0:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> One black dot. It's like an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.44,0:03:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain. That is consistent with the reconnaissance aircraft report.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.40,0:03:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop. Prepare to dive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.06,0:04:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,> Dive, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.85,0:04:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> There are no waves at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain. The periscope will be discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.85,0:04:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, I'm grateful that the enemy is stay in the direction of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.89,0:04:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,> Heaven's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.85,0:04:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, voyage chief. Your calculation was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.54,0:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> How far is it between us and the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes. We can catch up in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.13,0:04:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,> Check the torpedoes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:05:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,> At that time, only the Japanese Navy used compressed oxygen to propel its torpedoes. Max speed: 40 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.71,0:05:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The range is 4000m and the amount of gunpowder it contains is 500kg. It has the highest hit rate in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,> And again, the submarine itself has many world-class features, including high-speed power at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.06,0:05:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Its excellent performance, along with the German U-boat, shook each country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.99,0:05:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> How is it? > Captain, the weather is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:06:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's like a dream that there was such a fierce battle. > I am not asking about the weather, but the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes, even according to the previous report.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.51,0:06:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is it useless? But somehow we're back in Hawaii. I can't stay in such a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.61,0:06:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes, the destroyers are toeing us right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> Now, in our home country, they are doing their best to save an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.33,0:06:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for the time being, the remaining two ships, Enterprise and Hornet, must protect the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.99,0:06:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end, I want to return Yorktown to the battlefield as soon as possible. Fortunately there are no waves. Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain, the wind has come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,> The wind has come out. > Good. Heaven's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.37,0:06:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Lower the periscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,> They are doing it. They are on the alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy's vigilance is strict. Don't make noise inside the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.20,0:07:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Master of the voyage. Their current location doesn't fit the calculation. > Is the enemy being swept away by the wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, the enemy is moving. You've come behind the enemy for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> I'm sorry. > No, you don't have to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.54,0:08:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,> No matter how genius your navigation is, you can't get close to it exactly in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.75,0:08:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> It is dangerous to raise the periscope any further and approach. Yorktown engines are off, so it’s Impossible to follow their sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.68,0:08:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> Aren't the enemy destroyers making a sound? > Will you follow the sound of the destroyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,> Pass under the destroyer. You can't go through just one. If you pass under the destroyer on the other side, you can surely catch the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.71,0:08:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> It’s a battō-jutsu in the dark. let's go. Depth 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.16,0:11:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is it okay? > A two-hour dive in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.40,0:11:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> Depth 18. Raise the periscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.99,0:11:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's perfect. We are on the right side of the enemy. Thank you. Master of the voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.16,0:11:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, 500 meters is too close. Keep a distance of 800 or 1000. > The knack of battō-jutsu is in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:12:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> Did they stop all at once? > Seven destroyers at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.89,0:12:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,> We were discovered. > Let's shoot and run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.06,0:12:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> What time is it now? > 12:37.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.02,0:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's lunch time. The Americans have taken a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.54,0:12:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.61,0:12:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Ready to launch a torpedo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.30,0:12:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> Ready to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.30,0:12:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> Prepare
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.37,0:12:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.85,0:13:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> 70 depth. hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.51,0:13:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> 37 seconds, 38, 39, 40, 41, 42, 43, 44,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.47,0:13:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> We did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> 30 minutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy destroyer is moving, but not coming near.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy destroyer is approaching straight on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.51,0:14:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy ship is passing directly above. Enemy, depth charge launch, 2 shots
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.09,0:14:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> Full starboard
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> Enemy depth charges, 54 shots, 55
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.68,0:15:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> Turn on the emergency light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.71,0:15:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> Flooding!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.68,0:15:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> Rear, flooded!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,> Flooding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> Everything is useless, both vertically and horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.92,0:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> The battery is damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,> Gas outflow
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.85,0:16:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> 20 people in the back, move to the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.78,0:16:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain, depth exceeds 100m. This ship cannot exceed 75m.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.23,0:16:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> Trust Japanese shipbuilding technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.23,0:16:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> 20 people in front, move to the back. 1 ton drainage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.78,0:16:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,> Put on a gas mask. Connect usable electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.75,0:17:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> How many hours will the battery last? > About 2 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.85,0:17:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> Officer. How much air remains? > 40kg
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.23,0:17:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,> Good. If you do your best for two hours, the sun will set. The enemy will also run out of depth charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain. At your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.75,0:17:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> This is suffering from gas. > Was the mouse here? It's auspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.13,0:17:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,> Do you know I-170? > Is she the one sunk in Operation Hawaii?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.99,0:17:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> When 170 departed, the mice on the ship disappeared steadily, and 170 didn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,> I know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.54,0:17:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> As you can see, our ship has not been abandoned by the mouse. It will be absolutely okay. We will definitely be back in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,> Surgeon Chief, don't let this mouse die. > Yes. I will take responsibility for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.54,0:18:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> Don't laugh. The air becomes muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.82,0:18:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> 1-168 lost power. Not only did the propulsion motor stop, but it couldn't stay level.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.68,0:18:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, the air and seawater in the submarine's tanks begin to move on their own, and as a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the submarine either surfaces or sinks with a striking force.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.68,0:18:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are enemies on the sea. Also, it is not allowed to sink to the 4000m seabed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.85,0:18:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I-168 managed to balance her ship and tried to save time. The battle between sinking and buoyancy continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.75,0:18:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, based on this bitter experience of the I-186, the Japanese Navy completely remodeled the battery of their submarines to make them shock-resistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.33,0:18:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> The ship is flouting up. > Move everyone forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.44,0:19:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is human balance useless?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.30,0:19:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain. Let's prepare for what we should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.99,0:19:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain, prepare for suicide with torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> It is going up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.78,0:19:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain, I'm sorry. We are floating up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> How many minutes have passed since the sound of the depth charges disappeared? > 40 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,> Good. Get ready to engage. Hurry up. > Let's fight with all weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Man your stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> Enemy, three destroyers. 15,000m. They are moving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy does not seem to be aware, because we are in the sun's glare. They will soon find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.95,0:20:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Hurry up and get air and electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.06,0:20:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Put out smoke. > Alright, hide it with smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.09,0:20:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.57,0:20:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> Hey, have you ever seen the captain's angry face? That kind of person has luck. Do not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.47,0:20:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,> How much air did you get? > About 70 kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.78,0:20:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,> Enemy, distance 5000 meters > Make more smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.37,0:21:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,>We can use the motor. Is working. > Hurry up the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we can run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.54,0:22:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,> I can't hear the sounds of the enemy destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.02,0:22:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> What is it? > Just give this to the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.54,0:22:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> All the non-commissioned officers have gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.99,0:22:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> We wanted to thank you for something, but I didn't have any words, so I brought this instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.71,0:22:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.47,0:22:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain. Have a drink. > No, let's go down and drink with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.51,0:23:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> The captain hasn't eaten anything since last night. > Me? There was not enough training.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.47,0:23:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> Master of the voyage. It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.23,0:23:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> The captain of this submarine, who did not lose his mild-mannered personality, encouraged his men, and achieved his goals together. He was always calm and bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.30,0:23:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Reliable decisions, especially in extreme conditions, cannot be made without this calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.70,0:24:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.92,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, test your strength It you are a man, burn your hope
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.44,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you area man, don't let yourself down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I and you are men and men bleed the same bright red blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.51,0:25:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
